Amazon ECS (Fargate) practical – step by step

Create an AWS account and login to AWS Console

Create an IAM user with admin permissions

Install AWS CLI and configure it using aws configure

Install Docker on your local machine

Pull a sample image

docker pull nginx


Open Amazon Elastic Container Registry

Create an ECR repository named nginx-demo

Authenticate Docker to ECR

aws ecr get-login-password --region <region> | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin <account-id>.dkr.ecr.<region>.amazonaws.com


Tag the Docker image

docker tag nginx:latest <account-id>.dkr.ecr.<region>.amazonaws.com/nginx-demo:latest


Push the image to ECR

docker push <account-id>.dkr.ecr.<region>.amazonaws.com/nginx-demo:latest


Open Amazon Elastic Container Service

Create a new ECS cluster

Select AWS Fargate as infrastructure

Name the cluster ecs-demo-cluster

Go to Task Definitions

Create a new task definition

Select Fargate launch type

Set task name nginx-task

Set CPU 0.5 vCPU

Set memory 1 GB

Add container name nginx

Use ECR image URI

Add port mapping 80

Enable CloudWatch logs

Save task definition

Go to the cluster

Create a new service

Choose Fargate launch type

Select task definition nginx-task

Set service name nginx-service

Set desired tasks to 2

Select default VPC

Select at least two subnets

Enable auto-assign public IP

Create or select a security group

Allow inbound HTTP 80 from 0.0.0.0/0

Select Application Load Balancer

Create a new load balancer

Set listener port 80

Set target type to IP

Set health check path /

Create the service

Wait for tasks to reach RUNNING state

Open EC2 → Load Balancers

Copy ALB DNS name

Paste DNS in browser

Verify Nginx page loads

ECS practical completed successfully

***Cleanup steps (very important)

Delete ECS service

Delete ECS cluster

Delete Load Balancer

Delete ECR repository
